This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on March 31, 2020. The memorandum delegates certain functions and authorities under the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2020 to various government officials. The Secretary of State is delegated functions and authorities vested in the President by section 7426 of the Act, as well as several provisions of the Act in consultation with the Secretary of the Treasury. The Secretary of State, in consultation with the Secretary of the Treasury and the Director of National Drug Control Policy, is also delegated functions and authorities vested in the President by section 7211(a)(1)(C) of the Act. The Secretary of the Treasury is delegated functions and authorities vested in the President by several provisions of the Act in consultation with the Secretary of State. The memorandum states that these delegations will apply to any future public laws that have provisions similar to those referenced in the memorandum. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.